Frons above clypeus forming sharp ridge, the latter finely carinate, evenly; mesal portion of disc moderately convex in lateral view, evenly; anterior margin in dorsal view weakly arcuate in middle and laterally oblique; Ushaped frontal impression shallow. Temples convex, granulate. Occipital ridge indistinct. Antennae (
Fig. 9
) 1.8-2.0 times longer than pronotum.

